LinuxPPC is a catch-all name for all distributions of the GNU/Linux system for computers based on IBM's <nowiki>PowerPC</nowiki> processor.

It is also the name of a specific distribution that is mostly based on <nowiki>RedHat</nowiki>.

Linux/PPC (a more appropriate category name for all distributions) includes:

* Debian/PPC
* Yellow Dog Linux
* LinuxPPC
* <nowiki>SuSE</nowiki>

All of these have recent releases of EmacsForLinuxPPC as part of the distribution.
